        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 8. Pichidimas piru sp. n. (a) photomicrograph of a sagittal section of the tongue-like fold of the male atrium; (b) photomicrograph of a sagittal section of the adenodactyl; (c) photomicrograph of a sagittal section of the common ovovitelline duct and the female atrium. Abbreviations: ad, adenodactyl; co, common ovovitelline duct; ej, ejaculatory cavity; fa, female genital atrium; fc, female genital canal; g, gonopore; ma, male genital atrium; pv, prostatic vesicle; tl, tongue-like fold of male atrium." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4780286/files/figure.png" .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4780284>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 7. Pichidimas piru sp. n. Diagrammatic representation of the copulatory apparatus. Abbreviations: ad, adenodactyl; co, common ovovitelline duct; ej, ejaculatory cavity; fa, female genital atrium; fc, female genital canal; g, gonopore; ma, male genital atrium; ov, ovovitelline duct; pb, penial bulb; ph, pharyngeal pouch; pp, penis-papilla-like fold of male atrium; pv, prostatic vesicle; sd, sperm duct; sh, lateral sheath of male atrium; tl, tongue-like fold of male atrium." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4780284/files/figure.png" .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4780278>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 4. Pichidimas piru sp. n. (a) Photomicrograph (above) of a horizontal section of near dorsal epidermis and a diagrammatic representation of the section (below); (b) Photomicrograph (above) of a horizontal section near ventral epidermis and a diagrammatic representation of the section (below). Abbreviations: cc, circular cutaneous muscle layer; dc, double diagonal cutaneous muscle layer; dd, dorso-diagonal parenchymal muscle layer; de, dorsal epidermis; ls, normal longitudinal cutaneous muscles; pn, peripheral nervous plexus; sn, subneural transverse parenchymal muscle layer; sp, supraintestinal transverse parenchymal muscle layer; vd, ventrodiagonal parenchymal muscle layer; ve, ventral epidermis." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4780278/files/figure.png" .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4780282>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 6. Pichidimas piru sp. n. Photomicrograph of a sagittal section of the pharynx. Abbreviations: es, oesophagus; mo, mouth; ph, pharyngeal pouch." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4780282/files/figure.png" .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4780276>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 3. Pichidimas piru sp. n. Photomicrograph (a) and diagrammatic representation (b) of a transverse section of the pre-pharyngeal region. Abbreviations: cr, creeping sole; dd, dorsodiagonal parenchymal muscle layer; de, dorsal epidermis; gl, glands; i, intestine; ls, normal longitudinal cutaneous muscles; ov, ovovitelline duct; sd, sperm duct; sn, subneural transverse parenchymal muscle layer; sp, supraintestinal transverse parenchymal muscle layer; t, testis; vd, ventrodiagonal parenchymal muscle layer; vn, ventral nervous plate." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4780276/files/figure.png" .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4780280>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 5. Pichidimas piru sp. n. (a–c) Photomicrographs (above) and respective diagrammatic representation of the section (below) of transverse sections of the anterior section of the body, at 600, 400, and 100 µm from the anterior extremity. Abbreviations: an, anterior nervous system; dd, dorso-diagonal parenchymal muscle layer; de, dorsal epidermis; e, eye; i, intestine; ls, normal longitudinal cutaneous muscles; r, cephalic retractor muscle; sb, subintestinal transverse parenchymal muscle layer; sn, subneural transverse parenchymal muscle layer; vd, ventro-diagonal parenchymal muscle layer; ve, ventral epidermis." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4780280/files/figure.png" .

